 How to Make People Think You Are Confident 

Method 3 of 4:
Developing a Confident Lifestyle

1. Look and feel your best. Taking good care of yourself is important to your well-being. Your hygiene, attire, and health are all worth the effort, especially if you are trying to impress at a job interview or date. Appearance and first impression are very powerful. Looking sharp puts you at an advantage and makes others more receptive to you. You'll look good and confident at a glance.

👀Spend time each day on your hygiene. Shower, brush your teeth, and apply deodorant as often as necessary.
👀Wear clothes that you think make you look and feel good. Your self-confidence will get a boost if you wear clothes that put you at ease and make you feel comfortable.
